WEBVTT

00:02.003 --> 00:03.635
           NARRATOR:
       <i> Once upon a time</i>

00:03.670 --> 00:05.804
      <i> in a mythical place</i>
     <i> called Cape Kennedy,</i>

00:05.839 --> 00:08.774
<i> an astronaut named Tony Nelson</i>

00:08.809 --> 00:10.575
  <i> went up on a space mission.</i>

00:10.611 --> 00:11.876
      <i> The missile went up</i>

00:11.912 --> 00:13.445
   <i> but something went wrong,</i>

00:13.480 --> 00:15.447
<i> and they had to bring it down.</i>

00:15.482 --> 00:20.084
   <i> Captain Nelson landed on</i>
<i> an island in the South Pacific,</i>

00:20.120 --> 00:21.787
   <i> where he found a bottle.</i>

00:21.822 --> 00:23.822
           <i> At least,</i>
   <i> it looked like a bottle.</i>

00:23.857 --> 00:26.825
      <i>  But it didn't act</i>
       <i> like a bottle...</i>

00:26.860 --> 00:29.294
  <i> because in it was a genie.</i>

00:29.330 --> 00:32.063
     <i> Oh, not your average</i>
        <i> everyday genie,</i>

00:32.098 --> 00:34.098
   <i> but a beautiful genie...</i>

00:35.202 --> 00:37.435
   <i> who could grant any wish.</i>

00:37.471 --> 00:40.939
             [♪♪♪]

01:02.196 --> 01:03.929
<i> Captain Nelson was so grateful</i>

01:03.964 --> 01:05.663
     <i> he set Jeannie free.</i>

01:05.699 --> 01:07.599
       <i> Only she didn't</i>
       <i> want to be free.</i>

01:07.634 --> 01:09.467
      <i> You know how it is</i>
  <i> when you've been cooped up</i>

01:09.503 --> 01:11.870
  <i> in a bottle for 2000 years.</i>

01:11.906 --> 01:13.671
    <i> She wanted to have fun.</i>

01:13.707 --> 01:16.141
   <i> And she wanted to have it</i>
     <i> with Captain Nelson.</i>

01:16.176 --> 01:19.011
   <i> So she followed him back</i>
        <i> to Cocoa Beach,</i>

01:19.046 --> 01:20.379
        <i> a mythical town</i>

01:20.414 --> 01:23.248
      <i> in a mythical state</i>
        <i> called Florida.</i>

01:23.283 --> 01:25.317
   <i> And there in this house,</i>
    <i> the girl in the bottle</i>

01:25.352 --> 01:27.886
   <i> plays spin the astronaut.</i>

01:27.922 --> 01:29.788
             [♪♪♪]

01:29.823 --> 01:31.156
[SIGHS]

01:31.191 --> 01:34.659
Why must thou work
on such a lovely day?

01:34.694 --> 01:36.228
Couldest thou not
play hooky?

01:36.263 --> 01:38.063
We're testing some
new oxygen equipment.

01:38.098 --> 01:40.265
Somebody's gotta
be there to breathe.
                      Oh.

01:40.301 --> 01:41.733
                    A pity.

01:41.768 --> 01:42.734
                  The sky
               reminds me of

01:42.769 --> 01:45.003
             a bright summer day
                 in Baghdad.

01:45.039 --> 01:46.471
    Does it?
                      Mm.

01:46.506 --> 01:49.674
Say, has the weather changed
much in the last 2000 years?

01:49.709 --> 01:51.276
                 Oh, weather
                 is weather.

01:51.311 --> 01:53.411
        In ancient Persia
       we had an old saying:

01:53.447 --> 01:54.979
        "Everyone talks
       about the weather,

01:55.014 --> 01:56.648
          but no one does
        anything about it."

01:56.683 --> 01:57.782
        You're kidding?

01:58.785 --> 02:00.319
      I jest you not, master.

02:00.354 --> 02:02.787
           [LAUGHS]

02:02.823 --> 02:04.956
Well, Roger's gonna pick me up.

02:06.127 --> 02:07.359
 I better meet him at the door.

02:07.394 --> 02:10.829
      It wouldn't do to have him
           see you, would it?

02:10.864 --> 02:13.698
Hm. Oh, stay and play.
Do not go breathe.

02:13.734 --> 02:15.200
              You know, what I'd
               really like to do

02:15.236 --> 02:17.636
             on a day like this
              is go swimming.

02:17.671 --> 02:19.971
    I wish I had a swimming pool
            in my patio.

02:20.007 --> 02:21.106
             [♪♪♪]

02:27.281 --> 02:28.280
            Jeannie.

02:29.250 --> 02:30.215
                        Jeannie.

02:30.251 --> 02:31.583
 What will the neighbors think?

02:31.619 --> 02:33.118
I can't afford a swimming pool.

02:33.854 --> 02:35.153
        You do not wish it?

02:35.189 --> 02:36.554
     No, I do not wish it.

02:36.590 --> 02:37.722
  Now, come on, get rid of it.

02:39.593 --> 02:41.126
             Help!

02:41.895 --> 02:42.861
             Tony?

02:42.896 --> 02:44.429
                  Where are you,
                       Tony?

02:47.101 --> 02:48.066
       Tony?

02:48.101 --> 02:49.434
            Jeannie!

02:57.644 --> 03:00.412
             [♪♪♪]

03:05.419 --> 03:07.185
            Oh. Hi.

03:07.220 --> 03:08.653
          The name's Roger.

03:08.689 --> 03:11.389
              What are you doing
               down there, Tony?

03:11.424 --> 03:12.724
              Get me outta here.

03:13.694 --> 03:14.793
    [SIGHS]

03:18.532 --> 03:20.332
               Thanks. What am I
                gonna tell him?

03:20.367 --> 03:21.333
Oh, you will
not have to

03:21.368 --> 03:22.601
tell him anything,
master.

03:22.636 --> 03:24.436
He will remember
nothing of this.

03:24.471 --> 03:25.671
                       Don't be
                     ridiculous.

03:25.706 --> 03:27.705
                     Of course
                     he will.

03:27.741 --> 03:30.075
What are you standing there for?
We're gonna be late.

03:30.110 --> 03:31.276
       Yeah, yeah. You're right.

03:31.311 --> 03:32.277
Uh, listen, I--

03:32.312 --> 03:33.711
I've got a lot to do
around here.

03:33.747 --> 03:35.213
Uh, I'll meet you
there, okay?

03:35.249 --> 03:37.015
Uh, uh-- If I'm late,
you start without me.

03:37.051 --> 03:38.316
                        Start
                    without you?

03:38.352 --> 03:39.384
               Yeah.

03:42.556 --> 03:43.588
                   [DOOR CLOSES]

03:43.623 --> 03:44.722
      [WHISTLES IN RELIEF]

03:49.530 --> 03:51.596
    Boy, one of these days
        she's gonna...

03:51.631 --> 03:52.964
        [SIGHS]

04:02.876 --> 04:04.008
                 Jeannie.

04:06.012 --> 04:07.479
                     Jeannie.

04:07.514 --> 04:09.547
I'm sorry
about that, master.

04:09.583 --> 04:12.083
      That's all right, Jeannie.
      It could happen to anyone.

04:12.118 --> 04:13.317
            Well, almost anyone.

04:13.353 --> 04:14.886
               Say, where did
           we get the groceries?

04:14.921 --> 04:16.754
Oh, I went shopping
early this morning.

04:18.158 --> 04:19.124
      You left the house?

04:19.159 --> 04:21.059
    Yes. I had to hurry down

04:21.094 --> 04:23.228
   to my neighborhood grocer
    to shop for your supper.

04:23.263 --> 04:25.196
       Well, now who told you
            to do that?

04:26.433 --> 04:27.732
      A man on television.

04:29.236 --> 04:30.568
                  It figures.

04:31.805 --> 04:34.205
    Master?
                      Mm?

04:34.241 --> 04:35.373
Do you think
it is proper

04:35.409 --> 04:36.808
for a man
to strike a woman?

04:36.843 --> 04:39.010
              No. Of course not.
                     Why?

04:41.614 --> 04:42.581
        Did somebody hit you?

04:42.616 --> 04:44.783
           [SOBBING]

04:44.818 --> 04:46.551
          Yes, master.

04:47.687 --> 04:48.887
             Where?
        A-at the market?

04:49.790 --> 04:51.389
          Yes, master.

04:51.424 --> 04:53.291
    Would you recognize him
     if you saw him again?

04:53.326 --> 04:56.428
       Ooh, I shall never
        forget his face.

04:56.463 --> 04:58.563
              Come on, let's go.

04:58.599 --> 04:59.764
         Where?

04:59.799 --> 05:00.965
                    Well, down
                  to the market.

05:01.001 --> 05:02.300
                  Maybe we can
                still catch him.

05:02.335 --> 05:05.003
     Please, do not bother.
 You-- You have to go breathe.

05:05.038 --> 05:06.671
     I do not have to breathe.

05:06.706 --> 05:07.906
      I-it would be better

05:07.941 --> 05:09.908
         if you did not
 get involved in this, master.

05:09.943 --> 05:12.043
Involved? I'm already involved.

05:12.079 --> 05:13.211
  Now, nobody is gonna hit you

05:13.247 --> 05:14.780
       or any other woman
       while I'm around.

05:14.815 --> 05:15.781
        You take me to him.

05:15.816 --> 05:16.948
              Now?

05:16.984 --> 05:18.583
      Well, of course now.

05:21.254 --> 05:22.320
              Hey, where are we?

05:22.356 --> 05:24.089
We're at
the marketplace, master.

05:24.124 --> 05:26.057
Oh, and there's Ali,
the man who hit me.

05:26.093 --> 05:27.058
            Wait a second. Wait.

05:27.094 --> 05:28.159
                     That was
                 2000 years ago.

05:28.195 --> 05:29.427
          Yes.

05:29.463 --> 05:31.729
       Well, why were you crying
         about it this morning?

05:31.764 --> 05:33.131
I just remembered it.

05:33.166 --> 05:34.199
               You just remem--?

05:34.234 --> 05:35.600
              Come on, let's get
                 out of here.

05:35.635 --> 05:37.202
Ooh! You were insincere
when you said

05:37.237 --> 05:38.704
you would not
let a man strike me.

05:38.739 --> 05:40.472
             Well, I was sincere
                 at the time,

05:40.507 --> 05:42.474
             b-but that was 2000
                  years ago.

05:42.509 --> 05:44.308
             I mean, come on,
         let bygones be bygones.

05:44.344 --> 05:45.543
                   Yeah, well...

05:45.579 --> 05:47.645
    I'd love to avenge the wrong
        done to you, Jeannie.

05:47.681 --> 05:49.213
              But, well... Look,
              if I miss my test,

05:49.248 --> 05:50.915
            I'll have to explain
             to Doctor Bellows.

05:50.951 --> 05:52.216
                   And if I have
                    to explain,

05:52.251 --> 05:54.218
        he'll have me thrown out
         of the space program--

05:54.253 --> 05:56.053
                   Let's get
                  out of here.

05:56.089 --> 05:58.490
               Ah.
            It is you.

05:58.525 --> 06:00.758
So thou
hast returned.

06:01.728 --> 06:02.894
                   Uh, no, no.

06:02.929 --> 06:04.696
             Actually, we were
           just passing through.

06:04.731 --> 06:06.698
        We wanted to take a look
        at some of your carpets.

06:06.733 --> 06:09.601
       Come. I have been
       waiting for thee.

06:09.636 --> 06:11.435
           Ooh, you're
           hurting me!

06:11.471 --> 06:12.436
                     Yeah, yeah,
                        yeah.

06:12.472 --> 06:13.905
                Let her alone...
                      sir.

06:13.940 --> 06:17.342
Introduce me to your ludicrously
        costumed friend.

06:17.377 --> 06:20.712
This is Nelson, flier
through the moons of space.

06:20.747 --> 06:21.713
   This is Ali,

06:21.748 --> 06:23.682
                  killer of many
                    giant men.

06:23.717 --> 06:25.149
                  Killer of many
                 giant men, huh?

06:25.185 --> 06:26.184
       Do not fear.

06:26.220 --> 06:28.953
You are far too
puny and small

06:28.988 --> 06:30.389
for Ali
to bother with.

06:30.424 --> 06:31.690
             Come.

06:34.828 --> 06:36.228
           Hey. Hey,
      wait a minute, you.

06:37.063 --> 06:38.129
                   I told you
                to put her down.

06:38.164 --> 06:40.732
          Let go of me.
          Put me down.

06:40.767 --> 06:42.601
               Here, stand back.
                  Stand back.

06:42.636 --> 06:44.936
               All right, fella.
                 I warned you.

06:44.971 --> 06:46.504
                      [YELLS]

06:46.540 --> 06:47.572
             [GRUNTING]

06:51.745 --> 06:53.044
                      [YELLS]

06:54.414 --> 06:56.014
      [LAUGHS]

06:57.584 --> 06:58.750
            [GASPS]

06:58.785 --> 07:00.151
Ali deals with giants,

07:00.186 --> 07:02.620
but I'm gonna make
an exception in thy case

07:02.656 --> 07:04.589
and break thy neck.

07:04.624 --> 07:06.858
           Oh, I don't think so.

07:06.893 --> 07:09.427
     I'm gonna have to teach you
         a lesson, big fella.

07:09.462 --> 07:10.762
             All right, Jeannie,
                   get him.

07:12.231 --> 07:13.665
                Jeannie?

07:13.700 --> 07:14.699
                  Jeannie?

07:14.734 --> 07:16.468
        [LAUGHS]
                    Jeannie?

07:16.503 --> 07:18.369
        [BOTH LAUGHING]

07:19.839 --> 07:21.038
                   Look out!

07:21.074 --> 07:26.144
             [♪♪♪]

07:42.095 --> 07:45.063
Look, look. Look at this
fine specimen.

07:45.098 --> 07:46.465
   A slave among slaves.

07:46.500 --> 07:47.866
        What am I offered?

07:47.901 --> 07:49.334
Five shekels.
               Seven.

07:49.369 --> 07:50.869
            I have seven,
            I have seven.

07:50.904 --> 07:52.838
        Who will give me eight?
                 Eight?

07:52.873 --> 07:55.607
        Sold to Muphesta Kem
         for seven shekels.

07:55.642 --> 07:57.175
        [CROWD MURMURS]

07:57.210 --> 07:58.176
   Excuse me.

07:58.211 --> 07:59.478
            Oh, wait,
           wait, wait.

07:59.513 --> 08:00.479
        One was omitted.

08:00.514 --> 08:01.546
       What is thy name?

08:01.582 --> 08:03.014
Ah... Oh, Nelson.
I'm a tourist.

08:03.049 --> 08:04.315
I'm just
traveling through.

08:04.351 --> 08:05.851
A traveler.
             Ah!

08:05.886 --> 08:08.687
A man of culture
who can tutor thy children.

08:08.722 --> 08:10.889
         What am I bid
    for this fine specimen?

08:10.924 --> 08:12.691
   You don't understand, sir.
         I can't stay.

08:12.726 --> 08:14.626
        I'm on my way to
  a very important experiment.

08:14.661 --> 08:15.760
            Excuse me.

08:15.796 --> 08:17.028
                 Ah!

08:17.063 --> 08:18.730
   Mark that fighting spirit.

08:18.765 --> 08:19.998
            [LAUGHS]

08:20.033 --> 08:23.034
    This one you can harness
to the plow and spare the oxen.

08:23.069 --> 08:25.236
           He will work at home
          or toil on the fields.

08:25.271 --> 08:26.471
      How much do I hear?

08:26.506 --> 08:28.439
                  One shekel
             is all he is worth.

08:28.474 --> 08:30.708
          One shekel?
    I'm a college graduate.

08:30.743 --> 08:32.177
      I'm worth at least--

08:32.212 --> 08:33.211
      Let me out of here.

08:33.246 --> 08:34.846
    AUCTIONEER:
Did I not tell thee

08:34.881 --> 08:36.080
he was high-spirited?

08:36.116 --> 08:37.148
Three shekels.

08:37.183 --> 08:38.850
    Oh, three shekels.

08:38.885 --> 08:40.451
      He is worth
  20 times that many.

08:40.486 --> 08:41.486
          Look...

08:41.520 --> 08:42.919
Look at these teeth.

08:42.956 --> 08:44.756
           Oh. Oh, I have
         a lot of cavities.

08:44.791 --> 08:45.957
           I use the wrong
             toothpaste.

08:45.992 --> 08:47.726
           I-I appreciate
     your interest in me, sir,

08:47.761 --> 08:49.393
 but I am late for the office.
           Excuse me.

08:49.429 --> 08:50.461
                   Five shekels.

08:50.496 --> 08:52.296
       Do I hear six shekel?

08:52.331 --> 08:54.265
                Does he have
            any special talents?

08:54.300 --> 08:56.600
         Dost thou have
      any special talents?

08:56.636 --> 08:57.735
        Uh, no, not really.

08:57.771 --> 08:59.037
     Well, I'm a jet pilot.

08:59.072 --> 09:00.337
         He is a jet--

09:01.708 --> 09:03.374
      What is a jet pilot?

09:03.409 --> 09:04.909
           Forget it.

09:04.944 --> 09:06.644
     Do I hear six shekels?

09:06.680 --> 09:08.379
          Y-yes, yes.
     I'll bid six shekels.

09:08.415 --> 09:09.981
       You'll have my check
         in the morning.

09:10.016 --> 09:11.148
            When the banks open,
                    you--

09:11.184 --> 09:12.550
         Silence.

09:12.586 --> 09:13.818
        Sold to Mr. Bey

09:13.854 --> 09:15.019
               for five shekels.

09:15.055 --> 09:16.087
                Now, wait--
                   What--

09:16.122 --> 09:17.889
                 Come on,
               knock it off.

09:17.924 --> 09:20.291
           I happen to be
      Captain Anthony Nelson--

09:20.327 --> 09:21.292
                  Stop!

09:21.328 --> 09:23.294
               Now, come on,
                 I mean it.

09:23.330 --> 09:25.830
     Captain Anthony Nelson
 of the United States Air Force

09:25.866 --> 09:27.332
  on detached service to NASA.

09:27.367 --> 09:29.567
    Now, come on, I mean it.

09:29.602 --> 09:30.668
   Now, you and your friends

09:30.703 --> 09:32.737
        are gonna get in
        a lot of trouble

09:32.772 --> 09:34.538
         pushing around
    a United States citizen.

09:34.574 --> 09:35.673
       It could mean war.

09:36.343 --> 09:37.308
              War?

09:37.344 --> 09:38.409
           Yeah, war.

09:38.444 --> 09:40.278
    With the United States
         of America.

09:41.614 --> 09:44.615
What is this
United States of America?

09:51.491 --> 09:54.125
             [♪♪♪]

10:05.272 --> 10:07.272
What are you
trying to do, starve us?

10:09.742 --> 10:10.808
     Hey.

10:10.843 --> 10:12.410
Hey, this looks good.

10:12.445 --> 10:13.945
     Mm.

10:16.649 --> 10:18.749
Say...that is good.

10:18.785 --> 10:20.551
What is it?

10:20.586 --> 10:22.720
                  Goats' eyes.

10:25.225 --> 10:26.824
           It's a special treat.

10:26.859 --> 10:28.559
           Today is my birthday.

10:28.594 --> 10:29.928
   Yeah?

10:29.963 --> 10:31.629
How old are you?

10:31.664 --> 10:32.830
                    Eighteen.
   [GASPS]

10:34.100 --> 10:36.134
Well, how long
have you been here?

10:36.169 --> 10:37.768
                 Eighteen years.

10:39.472 --> 10:42.273
    Uh, uh, uh--
 W-what's your name?

10:42.309 --> 10:43.341
                    Turhan.

10:43.376 --> 10:45.009
Now, look, Turhan...

10:45.045 --> 10:46.477
is there any way
out of this place?

10:46.512 --> 10:47.478
                    Oh, yes.

10:47.513 --> 10:49.780
                  We all go out
                  the same way.

10:51.717 --> 10:53.084
Well, I'm not
going out that way,

10:53.119 --> 10:55.186
I can assure you.

10:55.221 --> 10:57.922
              Do not do anything
              foolish, stranger.

10:57.958 --> 11:00.425
                   They have
                 an expert here

11:00.460 --> 11:02.893
             whose only task
         is thinking of new ways

11:02.929 --> 11:05.964
        to cause exquisite pain.

11:05.999 --> 11:07.432
Well, don't worry
about me.

11:07.467 --> 11:09.267
I've studied
commando tactics.

11:13.173 --> 11:14.372
              You.

11:14.407 --> 11:16.574
Captain Anthony Nelson,
United States Air Force,

11:16.609 --> 11:18.876
serial number 36076A.

11:18.911 --> 11:21.079
And that's all the information
I'm required to give.

11:21.114 --> 11:22.146
Is there a Red Cross here?

11:22.182 --> 11:23.514
             Come.

11:23.549 --> 11:25.416
Majestic One
will see you.

11:25.452 --> 11:27.551
  It's about time I got to see
     somebody in authority.

11:27.587 --> 11:28.752
            [SCOFFS]

11:28.788 --> 11:30.788
    I'll put in a good word
      for you too, Turhan.

11:32.258 --> 11:34.392
             [♪♪♪]

11:34.427 --> 11:36.094
           GUARD:
           Halt.

11:36.129 --> 11:37.628
    Hey, hey, hey.
      What's--?

11:40.266 --> 11:43.300
                   So...thou art
                  the new slave.

11:43.336 --> 11:45.570
           They told me you were
          not right in the head.

11:45.605 --> 11:46.637
                  It be true.

11:46.673 --> 11:47.638
    [SCOFFS]

11:47.674 --> 11:49.540
It is not so.
I'm perfectly normal.

11:49.576 --> 11:52.343
          They tell me you come
         from a far-off country.

11:52.379 --> 11:54.712
Yeah. Only they don't
know how far off.

11:54.748 --> 11:56.514
                    And how did
                   you get here?

11:56.549 --> 11:58.549
I can't tell you.
                     Why not?

11:58.585 --> 12:00.317
You'd think I wasn't
right in the head.

12:00.353 --> 12:03.254
            Oh, peel me a grape.

12:04.323 --> 12:06.457
              [CHUCKLING]
            Don't be silly.

12:07.427 --> 12:09.193
           Hey, watch the shirt.

12:09.228 --> 12:10.595
                    Ah!

12:11.831 --> 12:14.098
             You really know how
               to hurt a fella.

12:14.133 --> 12:16.133
               I'm, uh...
       I'm sorry about all this.

12:16.169 --> 12:18.302
I-- I really don't
even belong here.

12:18.337 --> 12:20.705
                 I-- I don't
              even have a visa.

12:22.175 --> 12:23.407
                  [GRUNTS]

12:23.443 --> 12:25.142
             You're looking
       for a crack in the mouth.

12:27.213 --> 12:29.948
            I do not stand for
         insolence in my slaves.

12:29.983 --> 12:32.383
Now, wait a minute, lady.
Let's get something straight.

12:32.419 --> 12:33.918
      Ah!

12:33.953 --> 12:35.319
I am not your slave.

12:35.355 --> 12:37.988
I happen to be an officer
in my government's air force.

12:38.024 --> 12:39.457
                    Air force?

12:39.492 --> 12:40.658
     Yeah.
  Well, look,

12:40.693 --> 12:42.160
let's not go
into that right now.

12:42.195 --> 12:43.961
Look, all I want to do
is get out of here.

12:43.996 --> 12:45.229
I-I lost a friend of mine

12:45.265 --> 12:47.064
and I simply want to go
and search for her.

12:47.100 --> 12:49.133
                    Well, that's
                   your trouble.

12:49.168 --> 12:50.901
              You're preoccupied
                 with women.

12:50.937 --> 12:52.537
[NERVOUS LAUGH]

12:52.572 --> 12:54.972
         Well, I have someone
      who can take care of that.

12:55.007 --> 12:56.006
      Oh?

13:01.514 --> 13:03.914
I have been searching
everywhere for thee,

13:03.950 --> 13:05.116
son of a jackal.

13:05.151 --> 13:06.584
                  He needs to be
                      tamed.

13:06.619 --> 13:07.585
See to it.

13:07.620 --> 13:09.554
          ALI:
Oh, with great pleasure,

13:09.589 --> 13:10.955
Princess Fatima.

13:10.990 --> 13:13.124
       I wouldn't do anything
    I'm gonna be sorry for, pal.

13:13.159 --> 13:14.191
On your feet.

13:14.227 --> 13:15.460
              Now, oh--

13:15.495 --> 13:17.629
            Listen, if there's
         anything I can't stand,

13:17.664 --> 13:19.230
                 it's a bully
                who hits women,

13:19.266 --> 13:21.165
                  son of a pig.

13:21.200 --> 13:23.100
           And there's more
     where that came from, chum.

13:23.136 --> 13:24.869
 [SEETHING]

13:25.972 --> 13:28.306
Oh, I ask
thy permission.

13:28.341 --> 13:30.642
Let me break him in half
with my bare hands.

13:32.078 --> 13:33.678
         You have my permission.

13:35.047 --> 13:36.414
               Oh, I don't think
                 you're gonna

13:36.449 --> 13:39.150
break anybody in half
with your bare hands.

13:39.185 --> 13:40.351
Okay, Jeannie,
get him.

13:41.788 --> 13:43.921
Luncheon, Your Highness.

13:45.157 --> 13:47.091
     Now, come on, Jeannie!
      Stop fooling around.

13:47.126 --> 13:48.526
     I-I mean, this is you,
           isn't it?

13:48.561 --> 13:49.660
              Ah!

13:54.734 --> 13:57.802
  I came as quickly as I could
     to tell you the news.

13:57.837 --> 13:59.570
                   Oh, Mama.

13:59.606 --> 14:01.105
                    I can hardly
                    wait for you

14:01.140 --> 14:02.439
                   to meet
            your new son-in-law.

14:02.475 --> 14:03.741
            Oh, my dear.

14:03.776 --> 14:05.743
And what does he do
for a living, my daughter?

14:05.778 --> 14:07.879
                Oh, he flies
            through space, Papa.

14:08.982 --> 14:10.748
From this he makes
a living?

14:10.783 --> 14:12.483
                      He is most
                        clever.

14:12.519 --> 14:14.184
       When will the wedding
            take place?

14:14.220 --> 14:15.452
                    Oh, at once.
                Oh.

14:15.488 --> 14:17.354
           I wish you could have
            seen him attack Ali

14:17.390 --> 14:18.723
               and risk his life
                    for me.

14:18.758 --> 14:21.392
                Oh.
Our ancient proposal custom.

14:21.427 --> 14:24.529
     You shall be married here
           in your house.

14:24.564 --> 14:26.631
       I'll make the wedding
         arrangements now.

14:26.666 --> 14:29.366
                      [CHUCKLES]

14:29.402 --> 14:32.202
                Oh. I shall go
             and tell him, Papa.

14:32.238 --> 14:34.805
                  Oh, he'll be
                  so thrilled.

14:43.049 --> 14:44.682
                Think about it.

14:44.717 --> 14:46.216
            It's almost ready.

14:58.598 --> 15:00.631
I'm sorry I was
detained, master.
                   [GASPS]

15:00.667 --> 15:02.266
                  Jeannie,
            where have you been?

15:02.301 --> 15:04.201
I have been preparing
for my wedding.

15:04.236 --> 15:06.003
               Y-- Your wedding?

15:07.073 --> 15:08.405
                        Oh.

15:08.441 --> 15:09.840
                Oh, sure,
           you're back home now,

15:09.876 --> 15:13.410
             and you wanna
       settle down, get married.

15:13.446 --> 15:15.245
Are you not pleased?

15:15.281 --> 15:16.647
                   Oh, sure.

15:16.683 --> 15:19.383
         It's the best news I've
          ever heard in my life.

15:19.418 --> 15:21.819
         And you'll make someone
            a wonderful wife.

15:21.854 --> 15:25.022
Oh, I shall try
very hard.

15:25.058 --> 15:26.390
         It's a big day for you,
                isn't it?

15:26.425 --> 15:28.392
        Mm-hm.
   For both of us.

15:28.427 --> 15:30.327
                  Yeah, for both
                      of you.

15:30.362 --> 15:33.230
Oh, it will be
a beautiful wedding.

15:33.265 --> 15:36.400
                  Well...I wish
                 I could see it.

15:40.940 --> 15:41.972
                    Well...

15:42.007 --> 15:43.340
                     Say...
      Good.

15:43.376 --> 15:44.475
     Come.

15:45.311 --> 15:47.445
[GUESTS CHATTERING]

15:48.781 --> 15:50.247
        This is Nelson,

15:50.283 --> 15:52.083
          flier through
       the moons of space.

15:52.118 --> 15:53.450
         This is my mother.

15:53.486 --> 15:55.720
        Oh. Well, how do you do,
                 ma'am?

15:55.755 --> 15:56.754
                       Pleasure.

15:56.790 --> 15:58.355
And this is my father.

15:58.391 --> 15:59.890
                    TONY:
             How do you do, sir?

15:59.925 --> 16:01.325
Will you excuse us?

16:01.360 --> 16:02.493
    I, uh,

16:02.528 --> 16:04.462
think we should go attend
to our other guests.

16:04.497 --> 16:06.263
                      All right.

16:07.600 --> 16:10.033
        That's quite a wonderful
       girl you have there, sir.

16:10.069 --> 16:11.469
    It is sad.

16:11.504 --> 16:13.003
We were such
a happy family

16:13.038 --> 16:14.505
before the tragedy
overtook us.

16:14.540 --> 16:15.739
                Eh, uh, tragedy?

16:15.774 --> 16:18.075
When our daughter refused
to marry the wicked Jinn,

16:18.111 --> 16:19.776
and he turned her
into a genie.

16:19.812 --> 16:21.579
                          Oh.
                      Yes, that.

16:21.614 --> 16:24.548
           Well, every family
        has its little problems.

16:24.583 --> 16:26.083
                Will the wedding
                 be soon, sir?

16:26.119 --> 16:27.718
             I'd like to see it,
            but I really have to

16:27.753 --> 16:29.019
                  get back to
                  Cocoa Beach.

16:29.054 --> 16:31.522
What is this Cocoa Beach?

16:31.557 --> 16:35.159
              It's a little town
              east of...Baghdad.

16:35.194 --> 16:37.295
      I wish you will be
         very happy.

16:37.330 --> 16:38.296
                         Thanks.

16:38.331 --> 16:39.730
                   WOMAN:
            May Allah bless you.

16:39.765 --> 16:41.132
                        Well,

16:41.167 --> 16:42.333
                   thank you
               very much, ma'am.

16:42.368 --> 16:44.669
                 [BOTH LAUGHING]

16:44.704 --> 16:46.804
         I must say, your guests
         are certainly friendly.

16:46.840 --> 16:49.407
It is our custom to wish
the groom good luck.

16:49.442 --> 16:50.708
              The groom, huh?

16:53.179 --> 16:54.445
                The groom, huh?

16:54.480 --> 16:55.446
                   Jeannie.

16:55.481 --> 16:56.948
                        Jeannie?

16:56.983 --> 16:58.749
       Jeannie-- Oh, uh,
          pardon me.

16:58.784 --> 17:00.451
    Pardon me.
         Excuse us.

17:01.955 --> 17:03.855
I want to have
a little word with you.

17:03.890 --> 17:05.823
             What has happened
          to upset thee, master?

17:05.858 --> 17:08.692
Well, there's been some kind
of ridiculous mistake.

17:08.728 --> 17:10.794
Everybody here seems
to think that I'm the groom.

17:10.829 --> 17:11.963
            What is the mistake?

17:11.998 --> 17:13.531
      What is the mistake?
        You don't think

17:13.566 --> 17:14.832
 we're getting married, do you?

17:14.867 --> 17:16.968
          Well, of course.
    You proposed marriage to me.

17:17.002 --> 17:18.803
      I did no such thing.

17:18.838 --> 17:21.438
     Did you not attack Ali
and risk your life to avenge me?

17:21.473 --> 17:22.707
       Well, yes, but...

17:22.742 --> 17:25.209
       Well, in Baghdad,
that is a proposal of marriage.

17:25.243 --> 17:26.777
     Well, now you tell me.

17:26.813 --> 17:29.246
 Well, I'm afraid you're gonna
  have to call off the wedding

17:29.281 --> 17:30.881
or find yourself
another groom, or--

17:32.352 --> 17:33.718
             Yeah.
        Yeah, that's it.

17:33.753 --> 17:36.220
    You must have known some
wonderful chaps in the old days.

17:36.255 --> 17:37.954
  I-I do not want another groom.

17:37.990 --> 17:39.023
          I want you.

17:39.059 --> 17:40.091
            [SIGHS]

17:40.126 --> 17:41.292
  Jeannie, I can't marry you.

17:42.295 --> 17:44.128
            You hate me.
        You think I am ugly.

17:44.164 --> 17:45.930
       Of course I don't.

17:47.032 --> 17:48.332
 Then you will change your mind?

17:48.368 --> 17:49.966
        No. No, I won't.

17:50.002 --> 17:51.101
    And that's final.

17:52.638 --> 17:53.637
    So be it.

17:58.110 --> 18:00.678
     Nothing personal.
 I think you're beautiful.

18:00.713 --> 18:01.979
                     Oh, do you?

18:02.015 --> 18:04.214
            That won't help you.

18:04.250 --> 18:05.349
              The iron is ready.

18:05.384 --> 18:06.784
                  Let's start
               with your tongue.

18:06.819 --> 18:08.085
  For a man who's
   about to die,

18:08.120 --> 18:10.021
   you speak with
   a loud mouth.

18:10.056 --> 18:11.422
                   What are you
                  talking about?

18:12.458 --> 18:14.825
  Your hourglass
  is running out.

18:14.861 --> 18:16.527
What do you think
they're gonna do to you

18:16.563 --> 18:18.228
when they find that
Turhan has escaped?

18:18.264 --> 18:19.396
               Turhan's escaped?

18:19.432 --> 18:20.998
              That's impossible.

18:21.034 --> 18:22.733
          Turhan is in his cell.

18:22.769 --> 18:24.869
    [CHUCKLES]
  Well, I'm glad
  you think so.

18:26.305 --> 18:28.172
                I will find out.

18:28.207 --> 18:31.141
          And if this is a trick
              to gain time...

18:31.177 --> 18:32.142
                   when I return
                      to you,

18:32.178 --> 18:35.279
                 my pleasure
               will be doubled.

18:35.314 --> 18:36.847
        [CHUCKLES]

18:41.020 --> 18:42.954
            Jeannie.
     Jeannie, now come on.

18:42.989 --> 18:44.087
  Get me out of here, please.

18:47.760 --> 18:49.560
 [BREATHES HEAVILY]

18:49.595 --> 18:51.295
                    Do your arms
                   trouble thee?

18:51.330 --> 18:52.529
   Oh. No.
   No, sir.

18:52.565 --> 18:53.530
I was just, uh...

18:53.566 --> 18:55.599
I was just stretching.
                         Ah.

18:55.635 --> 18:57.401
             I would have a word
              with thee, my son.

18:57.436 --> 18:59.270
Yeah, and I would have
a word with thee, sir.

18:59.305 --> 19:00.871
I think there's
something we ought to

19:00.906 --> 19:02.005
get straight
right now.

19:02.040 --> 19:03.574
              Yes, of course.
                The dowry.

19:03.609 --> 19:05.743
Uh, the dowry?
Well, uh, that's it.

19:05.778 --> 19:07.210
There's just not
going to be--

19:07.246 --> 19:08.579
                 Yesterday a man
                   was beheaded

19:08.614 --> 19:09.913
               because he failed
                   to provide

19:09.948 --> 19:11.315
               sufficient dowry.

19:11.350 --> 19:14.652
           May Allah have mercy
          on his miserable soul.

19:14.687 --> 19:15.653
    Beheaded?

19:15.688 --> 19:16.787
                Tell me, my son,

19:16.822 --> 19:19.256
                 how many camels
                 dost thou have?

19:19.292 --> 19:20.824
    Why--
Why, none. I--

19:20.859 --> 19:22.593
                    None?

19:22.628 --> 19:25.596
Well-- Well, I mean,
I have none with me.

19:25.631 --> 19:27.364
                 [CHUCKLES]

19:27.400 --> 19:28.632
                 My daughter
                tells me that

19:28.668 --> 19:30.867
              thou art a prince
                among princes.

19:30.903 --> 19:33.370
Well, you know how
Jeannie exaggerates.

19:33.406 --> 19:34.838
          [BOTH LAUGH]

19:34.873 --> 19:36.307
                I would wager
                that thou hast

19:36.342 --> 19:39.443
                a king's ransom
              in goats and oxen.

19:39.478 --> 19:41.144
Yeah, well,
I-I can honestly say

19:41.180 --> 19:42.946
I have as many
goats and oxen

19:42.981 --> 19:44.682
as anyone
in Cocoa Beach.

19:45.884 --> 19:47.484
               I'm pleased
              to hear that.

19:48.854 --> 19:50.053
Would you
excuse me, sir?

19:50.088 --> 19:52.456
I, uh... I want to go
and see the bride.

19:55.227 --> 19:56.427
            Jeannie?
         Uh, excuse me.

19:56.462 --> 19:58.228
     May I have a word with you,
               please?

20:00.265 --> 20:01.732
                  Listen,
           when I get you home--

20:01.767 --> 20:02.899
 We are home, master.

20:02.935 --> 20:04.435
 Unless you would
 prefer a palace.

20:04.470 --> 20:06.269
               Do you know what
             you're doing to me?

20:06.305 --> 20:08.306
           Ali is waiting for me
              with a hot iron,

20:08.341 --> 20:10.607
     your-- Your father is ready
         to have me beheaded,

20:10.643 --> 20:12.576
          and I'm about to miss
         an important conference

20:12.611 --> 20:13.644
                in Cocoa Beach.

20:13.679 --> 20:15.779
That is more important
than our wedding?

20:15.815 --> 20:17.448
              [EXASPERATED SIGH]
                  I told you,

20:17.483 --> 20:19.116
         there isn't going to be
               any wedding.

20:29.628 --> 20:32.229
            So...thou tried to
                trick me.

20:32.264 --> 20:33.764
     Turhan was in his cell.

20:33.800 --> 20:35.900
  Well, you can't win 'em all.

20:36.969 --> 20:40.004
        Before I make thee sorry
            thou wert born...

20:40.039 --> 20:41.806
                 tell me where
                 the girl is.
    What girl?

20:41.841 --> 20:43.007
             The blond.

20:43.042 --> 20:44.608
         You were with her
        in the marketplace.

20:44.644 --> 20:46.610
     Somewhere you'll never
     get your hands on her.

20:46.646 --> 20:48.779
             Then thou shalt
              die in agony.

20:50.215 --> 20:52.349
    [LAUGHING]

20:52.384 --> 20:54.418
 Hey, come on,
  cut it out.

20:54.453 --> 20:55.786
    Jeannie.

20:55.821 --> 20:57.254
    [LAUGHING]

21:05.932 --> 21:08.899
          W-what is
          happening?

21:08.935 --> 21:10.500
         What are thou
          doing to me?

21:10.536 --> 21:12.770
 Now you can go and pick on
 somebody your own size.

21:13.840 --> 21:15.539
          Thou were willing to
              die for me.

21:15.574 --> 21:17.641
        Thou art the bravest man
           I have ever known.

21:19.145 --> 21:21.912
    Can we go back
  to Cocoa Beach now?

21:23.482 --> 21:24.849
                    Oh.

21:24.884 --> 21:27.484
              You may go back
              to Cocoa Beach.

21:27.519 --> 21:29.386
             [♪♪♪]

21:30.656 --> 21:32.522
                  I-I will never
                   forget thee.

21:33.592 --> 21:35.659
  Jeannie...

21:35.694 --> 21:37.461
I wish I could explain
how I feel about you.

21:37.496 --> 21:39.463
I think you're a wonderful
girl, but it just...

21:39.498 --> 21:41.398
Well, it just
wouldn't work out.

21:42.601 --> 21:44.301
                  [LAUGHS]

21:44.337 --> 21:46.003
            [SIGHS]

21:46.038 --> 21:47.471
           I'm home.

21:48.907 --> 21:50.141
        I'm home.
        I'm home!

21:50.176 --> 21:51.175
       [LAUGHS]

21:51.210 --> 21:53.110
           Jeannie--
     Hey, Jeannie, thanks.

21:53.146 --> 21:54.645
            Jeannie?

21:54.680 --> 21:55.746
    Jeannie, where are you?

21:57.283 --> 21:59.216
     Jeannie?
 Are you in here?

22:03.055 --> 22:04.421
        Jeannie?

22:07.260 --> 22:09.426
    This is goodbye,
       isn't it?

22:12.798 --> 22:14.665
           Isn't it?

22:17.069 --> 22:19.436
Well, Jeannie, wherever you are,

22:19.472 --> 22:21.405
     I want to thank you
       for everything.

22:22.941 --> 22:25.309
 You've been the greatest thing
   that ever happened to me.

22:26.779 --> 22:28.546
        And...

22:28.581 --> 22:30.847
if it means anything to you,

22:30.883 --> 22:31.848
I'll never forget you.

22:31.884 --> 22:33.717
                  That means
              a lot to me, Tony.

22:35.221 --> 22:36.554
                    To-- uh,

22:36.589 --> 22:37.688
                    who does
                  your shirts?

22:37.723 --> 22:39.056
       Huh?

22:39.091 --> 22:40.624
Roger, what are
you doing here? Huh?

22:40.660 --> 22:42.526
          What am I doing here?
        What are you doing here?

22:42.562 --> 22:44.528
        You were supposed to be
       at the lab two hours ago.

22:44.564 --> 22:46.129
            We tried to call you
             for the last hour.

22:46.165 --> 22:48.165
Oh, gosh, I'm sorry.
Come on, let's go.

22:48.201 --> 22:49.667
                Where you going?
               The test is over.

22:49.702 --> 22:52.002
Oh. Well, I'd better phone
the old man and apologize.

22:52.037 --> 22:53.270
                   Tony, are you
                   feeling okay?

22:53.306 --> 22:54.838
Well, I'm fine.
I'm just fine, sure.

22:54.873 --> 22:56.407
               You know what's
            the matter with you?

22:56.442 --> 22:57.608
            You're in a rut.

22:57.643 --> 22:59.142
          You need excitement
             in your life.

22:59.178 --> 23:00.611
                     Listen.
                 Do you remember

23:00.646 --> 23:02.680
         that Miss Universe that
           was here last year?

23:02.715 --> 23:05.048
         Well, she's back,
      and she's got a friend.

23:05.084 --> 23:06.083
          How about that?

23:06.118 --> 23:07.451
      Oh, no, no, no, no.
         Count me out.

23:07.487 --> 23:08.753
                 I won't take no
                  for an answer.

23:08.788 --> 23:10.988
                This Miss Galaxy
                  is a beauty.

23:11.023 --> 23:12.823
                 How about 8:00
                right here, huh?

23:12.859 --> 23:13.991
                And, uh--
             [CLEARS THROAT]

23:14.026 --> 23:15.593
    --do you have another shirt?
       Yeah.

23:15.628 --> 23:16.994
             Uh...wear it, okay?

23:17.029 --> 23:18.061
                      Ahem.

23:20.966 --> 23:22.065
                   [DOOR CLOSES]

23:22.101 --> 23:25.269
           JEANNIE:
<i> Miss Galaxy is a fat showoff.</i>

23:25.304 --> 23:27.304
They should call her
Miss Full Moon.

23:27.339 --> 23:29.206
                 I thought
                you'd gone!

23:29.241 --> 23:31.442
        [BOTH LAUGHING]

23:31.477 --> 23:33.577
I changed my mind.

23:33.613 --> 23:36.113
Oh, I could never
leave you.

23:36.148 --> 23:37.615
Did you really
mean it when you said

23:37.650 --> 23:39.950
that I was the greatest thing
that ever happened to you?

23:39.985 --> 23:41.351
            I refuse to answer
              on the grounds

23:41.387 --> 23:43.320
              I may incriminate
                   myself.

23:43.355 --> 23:45.656
          I'm sorry I made you
       lose face at the wedding.

23:45.691 --> 23:47.157
      [GIGGLING]
You should see Father.

23:47.192 --> 23:48.459
He's still looking for you.

23:48.494 --> 23:49.493
          [BOTH LAUGH]

23:49.529 --> 23:50.594
               I'll bet he is.

23:50.630 --> 23:51.695
              I tell you what,

23:51.731 --> 23:53.096
               we'll send him
              a herd of camels.

23:53.132 --> 23:54.398
        [BOTH LAUGHING]

24:01.574 --> 24:02.239
      Jeannie.

24:02.274 --> 24:03.674
Now, come on,
I'm leaving now.

24:03.709 --> 24:05.075
    W-will you stop sulking?

24:05.110 --> 24:06.844
I'm just gonna go to dinner
      and then maybe

24:06.879 --> 24:08.144
      take in a movie
       or something.

24:10.148 --> 24:12.515
